  "prompt": "What on earth should I be instead of a fashionista if I'm an artist that draws?",
  "response": "If you're an artist who draws, you might consider identifying with terms that more accurately reflect your passion and profession. Here are a few suggestions:\n\n1. **Illustrator** - This term is used for artists who specialize in creating images for various mediums, such as books, magazines, or digital platforms.\n\n2. **Graphic Artist** - If your drawings lean towards the digital and involve design elements, this could be a fitting title.\n\n3. **Sketch Artist** - If you primarily work with quick, detailed drawings, this term could suit you well.\n\n4. **Cartoonist** - If your style includes humorous or narrative drawings, often seen in comics or graphic novels, consider this title.\n\n5. **Visual Artist** - A broad term that encompasses various forms of art, including drawing.\n\n6. **Fine Artist** - If your drawings are considered more traditional or gallery-worthy, this could be a good fit.\n\n7. **Concept Artist** - If you create drawings to visualize ideas for films, video games, or other media, this title could apply.\n\n8. **Portrait Artist** - If you specialize in drawing people, this specific term might be more suitable.\n\nEach of these titles emphasizes different aspects of drawing and can help you better communicate your artistic focus and expertise.",
